        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the valve cover from the engine.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the rubber oil deflectors from the baffle assembly and discard.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean any RTV sealant from the underside of the valve cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the valve cover gasket is not damaged and in good condition, it can be re-used.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="2">
            <title>ASSEMBLY</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9412041">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9412042">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the four rubber oil deflectors on the baffle plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Be certain the oil deflectors for the breather baffle are secured to the baffle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check that the breather element is in the baffle with the nylon mesh up.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a generous bead of RTV sealant on the right hand oil deflector (push rod/exhaust
                    manifold side).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9412041" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9412041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         resolution="300"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring on the breather tube, and lubricate O-ring with clean engine oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Holding the valve cover above the engine, install the breather tube into the valve
                    cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Do not allow the cover to contact RTV sealant on the oil deflector until installation. If the
                        cover is lowered onto the RTV and then removed, the oil deflector will come off the baffle.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>The breather tube must be installed into the valve cover before the valve cover is lowered
                        onto the engine.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve cover assembly (with the breather tube in place) on the engine and
                    torque to 13 ft-lbs. (18 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install any remaining components that were removed. Fill with coolant (if drained) and
                    run engine. Check for leaks.
                </para>
            </step1>
